items.name: Handmade 2D Style - hand drawn Illustration style
items.description:
What is this?

Hand-drawn video game style that will add strong, black outlines to the objects in front and blur objects in the background to give depth to the image.

You can work with this style in the same fashion as described in this tutorial.

The style is so strong when used with 1.0 strength that the choice of the model is only a matter of composition and responsiveness to prompting.

The best results from the 8 models I tested with come from RealisticVision, Deliberate, CheeseDaddy'sLandscapeMixOffset.

Use a few of your favorite negative embeddings and general negative tags.

Quick example

positive prompt

(Award-winning photograph), (Japanese garden), (Autumn foliage), (Vibrant colors), (Fallen leaves), (Nature's beauty), (Red and gold hues), (Maple trees), (Reflections on water), (Peaceful tranquility), (Traditional wooden architecture), (Rustic bridges), (Soothing natural sounds), (Seasonal delight), (Serene garden views), (Low-angle perspective), (natural lighting), Nikon F2 Camera, hidden objects games, video game concept art, (8K Unity wallpaper), fine details, award-winning image, highly detailed, 16k, cinematic perspective, ((video game environment concept art style)), pretty colors, cinematic environment, (handmade2d:1.0) style

negative prompt

ng_deepnegative_v1_75t, bad-artist, bad-hands-5, (worst quality, low quality:1.4), multiple views, multiple panels, blurry, watermark, letterbox, text, character, human, people, 1girl, 1boy, NSFW, nude, signature, medium quality, deleted, lowres, comic, cleavage, frame, watermark, signature,watermark,signature

settings

CFG 7 and 50 steps on any model or the ones listed above

items.name: Claude Monet painting style
items.description:
Update:I make the V3 version which differs from the previous version in that the art style will now also affect the characters. In the past versions, for complex prompts, the style of the characters was still based on the base model's style, and only the background was affected by Lora. In this new version, I used the wd14-tagge to tag the captions, which has a greater global impact on the model. (Perhaps this has a greater impact on the base NAI model.)

This time I used LoCon instead of LoHa to make this model, as it seems that LoHa's performance is not very good.

This is the conclusion: In theory, if using stable diffusion 1.5, V2 might be better, but you need to add "a painting of" in front of the prompt. If you don't want this oil painting style to affect the characters, you can also download the V2 version. The V3 version only makes the style more influential on the characters, but this style may not be acceptable to everyone.

The following comparison image shows the difference between V2 and V3 on the effect of styles on people. (The image on the left is V3, and the image on the right is V2.)

Note:

This is a Lycoris model, and you need to install a1111-sd-webui-locon extension to use this model.

And don't use sd-webui-additional-networks to load this model.

Place the model in the path '.\stable-diffusion-webui\models\Lora' to use it.

Suggest weight:around 1 or higher.(But not suggest too higher,Of course, you can adjust it according to your needs.)

Optional tag: traditional media. (may enhance the effect)

The following is a description of the old version and does not apply to the new version.

Suggest weight: around 1 Or higher.(like 2,if you want)

Suggest CFG scale:1.5-3

Trained on 1,300 painting images by Claude Monet.

I once used native training to make it, but the results didn't seem as good as LyCORIS.

It is not guaranteed to work well with other LoRA , The art style may not affect the LoRa characters.(If that's what you want) .It is recommended to increase the weight and use low CFG scale.


Based on novel-anime-full model.

items.name: Lacus Clyne (Gundam SEED) LoRA
items.description:
Created to make peace between coordinators and naturals.

General Info

This LoRA has been trained using the Anything v4.5 model. It does a decent job at generating characters that look close to Lacus Clyne from the Mobile Suit Gundam series. The LoRA even has some variation when it comes to the style and pose she is displayed in and the clothes she wears. The model seems to also have some nsfw capabilities but they have not been tested.

Usage

The model has been trained using Kohya so you probably want to use it in the same way as you use other Kohya models. If you are Using A1111's Webui you want to move the file into the models>Lora directory. It is very important to use the relevant trigger word so that you can get results that look close to mine or even better. Sometimes you might get some lower quality anime screenshot like results. Thus you should get the best results with a weight of 0.6-0.8.

HOWEVER I think its a significant improvement over the Megan Fox that normal SD spits out.

items.name: 【Art Style】Nakamura Regura Style
items.description:
Introduction

A LoRA model trained with ~100 images by Nakamura Regura. The 784mb VAEs (NovelAI, Anythingv3, Orangemix, Counterfeit) are recommended. 0.6 ~ 0.8 weights are good. The preview images are generated using 1.5 version YesMix.

Cautions (Must Read)

  • Some preview images are generated using hires fix. Thus, if you wanna generate the preview images, pls download the original preview images and analyze them using 'PNG INFO' in webui to get all generating information.

  • The maximum of generating resolution should not exceed 1024 theoretically, otherwise extra/deformed head/limbs will be waiting for you :). Try to use 'hires fix' to prevent this problem and help to generate higher-resolution images.

  • For 784mb VAEs (NovelAI, Anythingv3, Orangemix, Counterfeit) users, make sure add '--no-half-vae' in command line of webui to prevent generating black images. See voldy's log for the details of edit method. For high-performance GPU, make sure 'medvram' and 'lowvram' mode are disabled.

items.name: Great Teacher Onizuka
items.description:
https://t.me/stdif_kos

Great Teacher Onizuka, officially abbreviated as GTO, is a Japanese manga series written and illustrated by Tooru Fujisawa. It was originally serialized in Kodansha's Weekly Shōnen Magazine from January 1997 to February 2002, with its chapters compiled into twenty-five tankōbon volumes. The story focuses on 22-year-old ex-bōsōzoku member Eikichi Onizuka, who becomes a teacher at a private middle school, Holy Forest Academy, in Tokyo, Japan. It is a continuation of Fujisawa's earlier manga series Shonan Junai Gumi and Bad Company, both of which focus on the life of Onizuka before becoming a teacher.

Due to the popularity of the manga, several adaptations of GTO were created, including a twelve-episode Japanese television drama running from July to September 1998; a live-action film directed by Masayuki Suzuki and released in December 1999; and a 43-episode anime television series produced by Pierrot, which aired in Japan on Fuji TV from June 1999 to September 2000. A second live-action series aired in Japan during 2012, and two more in 2014.

A sequel manga series, titled GTO: 14 Days in Shonan, ran in Weekly Shōnen Magazine from June 2009 to September 2011. Another sequel, titled GTO: Paradise Lost, began in Weekly Young Magazine in April 2014. Both the anime and manga were licensed in North America by Tokyopop. The anime series was re-licensed by Discotek Media in 2012. The manga is licensed by Kodansha USA.

As of November 2007, the manga had over 50 million copies in circulation, making it one of the best-selling manga series in history. In 1998, Great Teacher Onizuka won the 22nd Kodansha Manga Award in the shōnen category.

items.name: Two-person lora 双人lora 姐弟 Update for character Lora
items.description:
About v2：

做了优化，解决了过拟合的问题，现在可以不下调其他lora的权重，更好地适配角色lora了！寻找属于你的姐姐吧！

感谢hako-mikan！

感感谢大江户战士。

心得：使用tall girl,big breast等维持姐姐。

看在姐姐的份上，给我个5星如何:D

Optimization complete! Overfitting resolved, no need to adjust other LORA weights. Now better suited for character Lora. Find your perfect big sister!

Thanks to hako-mikan,

Thanks to CyberAIchemist！

Tips: Using traits like 'tall girl' and 'big breasts' to maintain the 'big sister' theme.

How about giving me a 5-star rating as a favor to your sister? :D

原文：

这是一个对于lora的性能测试。也许是第一个针对双人的lora？（如果有人见过请告诉我）。这回lora的训练目的是不针对外貌或者动作，而是针对两个角色的关系。所以我选择了这样一个关系（看trigger words）。

目前看来，效果是有的，但是也并不绝对稳定，少部分时候会出现黑白、单人等情况。不过它已经能大幅度提高tag的效果，以达到我们想要的目的。

我主要使用的是anything4.5+权重0.7。其他模型和权重还未能全部测试。可以结合其他的人物lora使用。

心得：1.记得用高清修复；2.其他lora适当降低权重；

请多多测试，给我反馈，谢谢！

This is a performance test for Lora. Perhaps it's the first test for a Two-person Lora? (Please let me know if anyone has seen one before.) The training purpose of this Lora is not focused on appearance or movements, but on the relationship between two characters. So I chose this kind of relationship (see trigger words).

For now, the results are good, but not completely stable. In some cases, it may show in black and white or only one person. However, it has greatly improved the effectiveness of the tags, achieving the goal we wanted.

I mainly use anything4.5 with weight 0.7. I haven't been able to test all the other models and weights yet. You can combine it with other character Lora.

Tips: 1. Remember to use Hires. fix; 2. Lower the weights of other LORA.

Please test it more and give me feedback. Thank you!

items.name: Xion (Kingdom Hearts 358/2 Days) LoRA
items.description:
This is my Xion LoRA. Xion is one of my more favorite Kingdom Hearts characters from one of my more favorite Kingdom Hearts games. I was feeling kinda burned out and noticed I hadn't made anything I wanted to make, so I made a character I liked.

Gathering the dataset for this character was pretty difficult. Getting official art was a pain in the ass because everything is in the .webp file format now (seriously, what's up with that), and fan art was equally sparse and often lacked quality.

This LoRA is good for a weight between 0.6 and 0.8. It will occasionally generate keyblade-like objects and sea-salt ice cream-like objects. It is also prone to generating dual-wielded ice cream, so look out for that. The casual outfit she has will generate less consistently than the Organization XII Cloak she is typically drawn in.

All pictures generated on my custom blends, available on my profile. I used Hires fix and Orangemix VAE.

Hori Kyouko Character LoRA

If you enjoy my models and want to support me you could buy me a coffee!

This LoRA mimics the character Hori Kyouko from Horimiya.

The example images were created with NeverEndingDream, AbyssOrangeMix and Dual Personality on varying weight (I recommend from 0.5-0.7 depending on the style you want) but feel free to experiment on your own. I tried briefly to mix it with a couple of different embeddings and it gave back decent results but you might find a better way to mix them (changing different weights etc.).

To change the weight just change the '1' in this prompt: <lora:hori-Kyouko-LoRA:1>.

I'd love to see the art you guys make with it so feel free to add them in comments.

How to use LoRA's in auto1111:

  • Update webui (use git pull like here or redownload it)

  • Copy the file to stable-diffusion-webui/models/lora

  • Select your LoRA like in this video

  • Make sure to change the weight (by default it's :1 which is usually too high)
